The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, June 14, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Book				 																																	(Hillary  Rodham Clinton) The former First Ladys memoirs are not just  a chronicling of her own life, from student activist to lawyer  and life in the White House as the Presidents wife, but also  a take on world events, some of which most people are still  unaware of. It tells the story of an ordinary girl from Middle  America who is now a New York Senator  The Film				 																																	(Max  Mueller Bhavan, June 16, 5.30 pm) Filmed by Anand Patwardhan  (picture above) over three years in India, Pakistan, Japan  and the US, the documentary portrays peace activism in the  face of global militarism and war. The filmmaker will conduct  a Q amp;A session after the screening  The Play 
	(Rabindra Sadan, June 16, 6.30 pm) The musical play will  be performed by Shatabdi Roy (picture above) Soumitra Mitra  and Srikanta Acharya, followed by an interactive poetry  recital by Roy and Mitra 
 The album				 																																	(Various)  The album is a product of a workshop by Swayam, an NGO working  with deprived women. And it is their dreams and pledges that  the lines speak of. Set to tune by Sankho Banerjee, the songs  are sung by established names Lopamudra Mitra, Indrani Sen  and Usha Uthup as well as upcoming talents Neepabithi Ghosh  and Annie Chatterjee 

